<br>
My point was as a cleric I am sick of watching pally/sk's in groups try and get agro as much as possibe.  Yes, its wonderful you can stun the hell out of anything or dot/snare it into oblivion and you will get agro.  No big surpirse there.  I am just sick of it as a cleric because honestly its a huge pain in my arse to have to play babysitter and watch people who should know how to play their class.  Pally's don't have to chain stun every mob that comes in, they will do more damage if they just melee the darn thing, but for some reason unknown to me they feel the need to chain stun for a few rounds of combat to get it on them, then they laugh about it in group chat.  I have seen people like this and they are on my no group list.  SK's don't seem to be as bad about it as pally's. /shrug<br>
<br>
Oh and I had a problem in my guild with a person (druid) who thought it was really cool to nuke a mob till it summoned them every raid, they were warned then removed.  The bottom line is people should know how to play their class, and if they don't I will ask them nicely one time to figure it out, after then if they keep it up they score some idiot points and I never deal with them again.  That is what it is all about knowing what to do with your class to contribute to a group not slow it down or screw it over.<br>
