<br>
I'm not talking tables here - no one tanks naked. Look at the warrior-only armors like champion's, myrmidon's, and warlord's - always higher AC and HP than hybrid stuff.<br>
<br>
So what if the stat caps are the same? Ever see a warrior and a pally/SK in the same gear at the same level with the same AA's - guess who has more HP and AC ?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My my, aren't we trying to be clever? See, clever only works if you know what you're talking about. So let me clue you in moron. AC has NOTHING to do with mitigation. NOTHING. Mitigation works in a simple way, look at disc defensive or combat stability. Every hit gets a certain % knocked off. So, at 10% mitigation, 1000 becomes 900.<br>
<br>
AC doesn't work like that. AC CANNOT alter a mobs maximum hit damage. Just like ATK bonuses can't change how hard your maximum non-crit hit is. AC stacks against ATK rating. On certain mobs, the ATK is high enough so that no matter how much AC you have, it won't matter.<br>
<br>
If you want an illustration of how AC works, fight AoW. AoW has a very high ATK rating. I don't think anyone can attain high enough AC to match his ATK. Therefore, warriors and knight armor class willl do nothing against AoW. Therefore, aside from the minor differences in avoidance caps, there will be no difference in the amount of damage absorbed between warrior and knight unless warrior uses /disc.<br>
<br>
As for not talking about tables. Tables determine your tanking ability. The fact that you relate tables exclusively to tanking naked shows exactly how little you know. So get a clue before your spew junior. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wilhelmm D'averam<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Overlord of the Apocalypse</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
